products.description: 30 years of experience building custom made cabinetry. We have the ability to & knowledge to build you the furniture pieces you deserve. UNFINISHED RAW This is a part of our economical line of benches. Built with value in mind. Corner Bench with storage beneath seating. Great space saver. No chairs to clutter the major walkways of your kitchen. Measures 60" x 60" x 18" deep x 16" high. The 16" height allows for a minimum of 3" for seat cushions. Our measurements are based on the "OVERALL" desired length. These "OVERALL" dimensions take into account the 18" deep corner on either side. Example: a 60" x 60" bench cannot fit into a space any smaller than the 60" x 60" footprint. You can always send us the size of the table or the space you are trying to fit the bench into for accurate sizing. Understanding how to order the correct size . Sizing is orientated from left to right when standing in front of the bench & looking at the bench. A 36" x 60" is therefore 36" on the left, overall length, & 60" on the right, again overall length, when standing in front of the bench & looking at the bench. These are overall dimensions when the sections are combined. 18" on the left + the 18" depth of the right = 36" plus two 30" sections to create the 36 x 60. A 48" x 60" bench would be comprised of, for example, 1 - 31" bench on the left & 2 - 30" on the right. this takes into account the corner. See last pic in listing gallery. Cushions not included. prairiewoodworksllc.com Our benches are made out of Maple & Fir plywood & solids to give you the strength & durability that you deserve. Our benches are built to last. These are paint grade benches. Please read our reviews to see what our customers have to say. Assembly Required. We can fully customize these bench seats. We can add drawers or we can leave the area under the bench seat open for a mudroom application. Please let us know your size specifications so that we can provide you pricing. We do not use "soft close" hinges as they do not adequately exist for bench seat tops. While soft close hinges work great in a vertical application, i.e. cabinet doors in your kitchen, they fail to work when the door/lid is in a horizontal position. NOTE When considering the bench or banquette for your home please keep this crucial point in mind. Insist that the bench that you having custom built for you is not made using MDF sheet products, a type of sheet material similar to particle board & is inferior to traditional plywood. MDF is used as a "cost saving" material only. However, it will be labeled as a material that is preferable to solid wood because of its stability over "solid wood", without mention of its comparability to that of plywood. Unfortunately, this material MDF, when exposed to water, will act as a sponge absorb the water & begin to deteriorate the integrity of the bench quickly. The most common scenario is a spilled drink on the floor that would migrate to the contact points of the bench on the floor.
